    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Is it not the case that specifying `monospace` for `code` and `pre` is unnecessary (look, I'm trying to speak your language, Min!), since that's the default in all browsers? A reason to keep it in would be if we wanted to have a preference for a specific kind of font, and use monospace as a fall back, but as is, the font-monospace we have for `code` and `pre` that comes from style.css now is still redundant (i.e. removing it from there still keeps the resulting styling the same as it is now).\n"
  },
